{"type":"message","id":"d8157895","parentId":"46c48071","timestamp":"2026-05-13T07:38:29.931Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Unity process seems to have started executing the pipeline but the log is very short (ended at 15:38:16). The issue is that the `Start-Process` with `-NoNewWindow` might not have waited for the Unity process to complete.\n\nLet me check - the Unity process (PID 13776) has already exited. The log only shows up to \"begin 'Excute Pipline:打资源(打资源前需确认宏正确)'\" at 15:38:16, but there's no conclusion or further steps logged. \n\nWait - I need to re-read the log more carefully. The Unity process exited very quickly. Let me check if it was actually running properly or if it crashed.\n\nActually, looking at the log again:\n1. \"Initialize BuildPipeline: Suspend\" - pipeline was initialized in suspend mode\n2. \"Resume the build step\" - resumed\n3. \"begin 'Excute Pipline:打资源(打资源前需确认宏正确)'\" - started executing the pipeline\n\nBut then the process ended. This could mean:\n- The pipeline failed quickly\n- The pipeline completed very fast (unlikely for a resource build)\n- The Unity quit parameter caused it to exit\n\nWait - the `Start-Process` command I ran earlier had `-NoNewWindow` and `-PassThru`. The PowerShell script logged \"Unity 进程已启动\" and then completed. But the Unity process (13776) ran separately. When I check if it's running, it's already gone.\n\nLet me also look at the log file more carefully to see if there's more content. The log might have been cut off. Let me check the exit code from the Unity process and see if the log file has more content at the end.\n\nActually, let me also check - maybe the Unity process crashed or the pipeline threw an exception. Let me see if there's a more complete log.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_AVqzq19tdInXItrO3BBb9188","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$logFile = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPi