{"type":"message","id":"3d3a8b54","parentId":"dc9a43de","timestamp":"2026-05-13T07:38:35.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear: **No valid Unity Editor license found**. Unity exited with return code 1 because it couldn't validate the license in batch mode. This is a known issue with Unity 2020.3.49f1c1 (Chinese edition) - the license validation fails in headless/batch mode.\n\nThe log shows:\n1. Licensing tried to connect, had some errors\n2. \"No valid Unity Editor license found. Please activate your license.\"\n3. \"Exiting without the bug reporter. Application will terminate with return code 1\"\n\nSo the pipeline never actually ran. This is the common licensing issue mentioned in the TOOLS.md notes - \"运行需要管理员权限（Unity 许可证校验）\".\n\nWait, but actually the main agent might have known about this. Let me check if there's something else we can do. The TOOLS.md mentions that running needs admin privileges. Let me try running it with admin/elevated permissions.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Unity 因许可证验证失败退出（exit code 1）。日志显示「No valid Unity Editor license found」。尝试以管理员权限重新运行。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_0Wen9kIPaukYZq7CFfli0941","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$logFile = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\"\nClear-Content $logFile\n\n$unityPath = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Unity.exe\"\n$projectPath = \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\"\n$method = \"YYZY.BuildPipeline.BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline\"\n\nWrite-Host \"正在以管理员权限启动 Unity 热更流水线...\"\n$process = Start-Process -FilePath $unityPath -ArgumentList \"-quit -batchmode -projectPath `\"$projectPath`\" -executeMethod $method -logFile `\"$logFile`\"\" -PassThru -Verb RunAs\nWrite-Host \"Unity 管理员进程已启动，PID: $($process.Id)\"\nWrite-Host \"日志文件: $logFile\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"dee